@node "introduction" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Introduction"

  This is a software to connect the PalmPilot PDA from 3com to the Amiga.

  With this software you can install programs to the PalmPilot, remove programs
  or purge the ram of the PalmPilot.

  You can even make complete backups of your PalmPilot`s ram and reinstall them
  completely. PalmGUI only bakup edited files, so you always have an actual
  image of the PalmPilot`s data on you Amiga.
 

@endnode

@node "requirements" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Requirements"

 Software:

  * MUI 3.8 or better
  * OS 3.0+
  * palmlink.library V1.2 or better (included)

 Hardware:

  * any Amiga
  * 3com`s PalmPilot

@endnode

@node "features" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Features"

 It currently supports the following hotsync types:

  * installing DB
  * deleting DB
  * fetching DB
  * purge the PalmPilot`s ram
  * complete backup
  * complete reinstall

 PalmGUI supports Drag `n Drop.


@endnode

@node "installation" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Installation"

 Just copy it to any place on your HD and make sure, that you have
 installed palmlink.library.

@endnode

@node "usage" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Usage"

 PalmGUI ist very easy to use. If you have used a FileManager before, you will easily
 be able to use PalmGUI.

 After the first start, you have to scan the DB`s of your PalmPilot by pressing the
 DB-List button. This data will be stored, and you only have to reload it again, if
 you delete or install a DB without the help of PalmGUI.

 Now the DB`s will be listened at the listview "Your Pilot". "Your AMIGA" shows the
 files of you computer. Now you can use the button:

 * Fetch:    to copy a DB to the active directory
 * Install:  to install a selected DB from "Your AMIGA" to the PalmPilot
 * Delete:   to delete the selected DB from "Your Pilot"
 * Purge:    to purge the Pilot`s ram

 You can also use Drag `n Drop to install DB, just drop the PalmPilot program
 into the "Your Pilot" listview.

 After you have selected the actions, you have to press the "Start HotSync" button.
 Now the HotSync will start.

 The "Backup" button will open a new window. Here you can start a complete backup of
 your Pilot`s ram, or a complete reinstallation of a backup.



@endnode

@node "preferences" "PalmGUI 3.10 - Preferences"

 Device:         here you can set the device (serial.device for standard amigas)
 Unit:           here you can set the unit (Unit 0 for standard amigas)
 Baudrate:       here you can set the Baudrate (57600 for fast amigas with standard serial)

 Palm Programms: enter the path were your PalmPilot programms are stored
 Palm Data:      enter the path were your Backup Data will be stored

@endnode


